.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1441,1270,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1270,1294]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman and Salvin, [1894]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1894" box="[541,986,1270,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Echelatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[541,658,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Echelatus</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1894]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1000,1052,1270,1294]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille, 1883" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varius">
<emphasis box="[1147,1337,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Anastrus varius</emphasis>
Mabille, 1883
</taxonomicName>
, which is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Butler and Druce, 1872))" baseAuthorityName="Butler and Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[724,1287,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Anastrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sempiternus">
<emphasis box="[724,982,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Anastrus sempiternus</emphasis>
(Butler and Druce, 1872))
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1300,1368,1302,1326]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[192,275,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,214,1144]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[192,1440,213,1144]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Genomic trees of Erynnini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677247" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677247/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Species of this new genus were placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1894" box="[625,700,1334,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,700,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[714,766,1334,1358]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson, 1868" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[861,1295,1334,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leucochitonea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lassia">
<emphasis box="[861,1106,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Leucochitonea lassia</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1868
</taxonomicName>
) previously, key to E. 
<quantity box="[296,397,1366,1390]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27254" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" unit="in" value="50.1">50.10 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[405,565,1366,1390]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, and were defined as the “pelopidas” group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[1132,1296,1366,1390]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref26367" refString="Austin, G. T. 2000. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: &quot; Antigonus &quot; genus group (Pyrginae), with taxonomic comments and descriptions of new species from Brazil and Guatemala. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 54 (1): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2000">Austin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
who gave a detailed morphological diagnosis on p. 5 and 7, which is not repeated here. Most importantly, the two unique diagnostic characters are: vinculum in male genitalia is expanded dorsad on both sides to cover most of tegumen and uncus arms are very short. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly 
<date box="[228,332,1494,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="1735-08-01">1735.8.1</date>
:T625C, aly3616.13.2:A50G, aly 
<date box="[705,808,1494,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="1036-05-01">1036.5.1</date>
:A436C, aly 
<date box="[945,1049,1494,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="1735-08-01">1735.8.1</date>
:C695T, aly 
<date box="[1182,1285,1494,1518]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" value="1735-08-01">1735.8.1</date>
:A772C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,1534,1591]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1534,1558]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, for the vinculum expanded as a hood over tegumen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,1606,1694]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,431,1606,1630]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[437,607,1606,1630]" genus="The" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" rank="species" species="pelopidas">The pelopidas</taxonomicName>
species group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[949,1117,1606,1630]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref26367" refString="Austin, G. T. 2000. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: &quot; Antigonus &quot; genus group (Pyrginae), with taxonomic comments and descriptions of new species from Brazil and Guatemala. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 54 (1): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2000">Austin (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, which consists of the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1440,1607,1631]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Austin, 2000" authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="2000" box="[293,637,1638,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis box="[293,470,1638,1662]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon cristata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[478,637,1638,1662]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref26367" refString="Austin, G. T. 2000. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: &quot; Antigonus &quot; genus group (Pyrginae), with taxonomic comments and descriptions of new species from Brazil and Guatemala. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 54 (1): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2000">Austin, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ehrmann, 1907" authorityName="Ehrmann" authorityYear="1907" box="[649,1097,1638,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leucochitonea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jason">
<emphasis box="[649,895,1638,1662]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Leucochitonea jason</emphasis>
Ehrmann, 1907
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille and Boullet, 1917" authorityName="Mabille and Boullet" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="ozema" variety="exstincta">
<emphasis box="[1109,1269,1638,1662]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon ozema</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1333,1440,1639,1662]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">exstincta</emphasis>
Mabille and Boullet, 1917
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Austin, 2000" authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="2000" box="[523,866,1670,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[523,700,1670,1694]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon simplex</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[707,866,1670,1694]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref26367" refString="Austin, G. T. 2000. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: &quot; Antigonus &quot; genus group (Pyrginae), with taxonomic comments and descriptions of new species from Brazil and Guatemala. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 54 (1): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2000">Austin, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Austin, 2000" authorityName="Austin" authorityYear="2000" box="[932,1361,1670,1694]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mylon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argonautarum">
<emphasis box="[932,1194,1670,1694]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Mylon argonautarum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Austin" box="[1201,1361,1670,1694]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref26367" refString="Austin, G. T. 2000. Hesperiidae of Rondonia, Brazil: &quot; Antigonus &quot; genus group (Pyrginae), with taxonomic comments and descriptions of new species from Brazil and Guatemala. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 54 (1): 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2000">Austin, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
